As part of the measures to stop the spread of the corona virus pandemic, the Chairman, Cross River State Universal Basic Education Board (CR-SUBEB), Dr. Stephen Odey, has donated solar energy power and medical facility to Uchu Yache community health centre in Yala Local Government Area of the State. Presenting the items at the Comprehensive Primary Health Centre in Uchu Yache  of Cross River State, Dr. Odey noted that the solar energy will provide 24 hours electricity and the medical facility will also provide a healthy leaving to the communities around. Dr. Odey said, “This solar energy is to ensure quality services for all at the health centre and, it will go a long way to ameliorating the condition of the total lack of electricity in the area,” he said. He called on the citizens to utilize and protect the facility for the benefit of the highest majority in the community. As he restated his commitment to stop the spread of coronavirus, he called on the people to observe ethics of hygiene and follow instructions of federal government to stay at home and stay healthy in the face of the global epidemic ‘COVID-19’. “As we wash our hands with soup and water constantly and consistently, avoiding crowded area, adding that God bless us all as we overcome these trying moments of the epidemic”. CR-SUBEB boss further said that he will support his state Governor, Senator Ben Ayade in addressing any challenging facing the state.